 DOM Manipulation Basics

Today's Focus: Document Object Model, Selecting Elements, Changing Content
What I Learned: DOM is a tree structure of HTML elements, accessed via JavaScript. Learned:

getElementById() – select single element by ID

getElementsByClassName() – select multiple elements by class

querySelector() – CSS selector for single element

querySelectorAll() – CSS selector for multiple elements

Changing content: innerHTML, textContent, innerText

Changing styles: style.property

Changing attributes: setAttribute(), getAttribute()

Practice Example: Theme Switcher

<button id="themeBtn">Dark Mode</button>
<div id="content">Hello World</div>

<script>
document.getElementById('themeBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
    let content = document.getElementById('content');
    content.style.backgroundColor = '#333';
    content.style.color = 'white';
    this.textContent = 'Light Mode';
});
</script>

Practice Questions:

Create page with heading and button that changes heading text when clicked

Make color picker that changes background color of page

Build show/hide password functionality in form

